data.content:
Created both files. Here's a summary:

**`SortableList.razor`** — Renders each item via `ItemTemplate` with **Move Up** / **Move Down** buttons. Buttons are disabled at the list boundaries.

**`SortableList.razor.cs`** — Code-behind with:
- `@typeparam TItem` for generic support
- `Items` parameter (`IReadOnlyList<TItem>`) — the incoming list is copied into an internal `_items` list in `SetParametersAsync`, so the parent's list is never mutated
- `ItemTemplate` (`RenderFragment<TItem>`) — consumer-defined rendering
- `OnOrderChanged` (`EventCallback<IReadOnlyList<TItem>>`) — fires after each swap with a read-only snapshot

Usage matches your example:

```razor
<SortableList Items="@tasks" OnOrderChanged="HandleReorder">
    <ItemTemplate>
        <span>@context.Title</span>
    </ItemTemplate>
</SortableList>

@code {
    void HandleReorder(IReadOnlyList<TaskItem> updated) {
        tasks = updated.ToList();
    }
}
```
